 of the event (if supported).
\par These last two options require further explanation. Archiving an event means that it is kept to one side and not displayed in the normal event listings unless you specifically ask to view the archived events. This is useful for
 keeping events that you think may be important or just wish to protect. Once an event is archived it can be deleted or unarchived but you cannot accidentally delete it when viewing normal unarchived events.
\par The final option of generating an MPEG video is still somewhat experimental and }{\deleted\revauthdel1\revdttmdel-1501387865\insrsid7562726\delrsid12872856 it's}{\cf0\revised\revauth1\revdttm-1501387865\insrsid12872856 its}{\insrsid7562726 
